channel.title: How to pass out or faint
channel.description:
Step One: Crouch on your knees and take 15-18 slow, deep breaths.
Step Two: On the 19th breath, hold it in and stand up
Step Three: Use your palms and squeeze your jugular vein(s) with a moderate squeeze
Step Four: Find something soft to land on
This is more better known as "Choking Out" or "The Pass Out Game"
Please note this can cause serious damage (Brain Damage, Stroke, etc) please, for the sake of your own life, understand the risks of doing this.
In my experience however, when I do it on my trampoline for a soft landing, as soon as I come to, I have an extreme sense of Euphoria.
Enjoy :)

Were you late to the Information Age or some shit cuz you aint that much older than me and I’ve always had a pc to type shit on since I’ve been old enough to need to type shit Though, we did have a typewriter, but I never had to use it for anything :/[/quote]

Yup, I was late. I didn’t have a computer till we got a 486 in 96ish? And I didn’t get internet until 2003 or 2004. But I’ve always had bad handwriting and some teachers required me to type papers when everyone else could handwrite them, so I used an electric typewriter.

The whole world spins, I lose vision completely…I feel like the floor got tipped upside down and I’m falling, and in some extreme cases I black out right after. item.title: How to pass out or faint
item.dc:creator: @goatee goatee
item.description:
@goatee wrote:

[quote=“jme, post:63, topic:275216”][quote author=Niall link=topic=363580.msg2900981#msg2900981 date=1249512234]

Easier way but not garunteed to work, but potentially less dangerous.
Lay down on a couch watching tv for a good hour or two (three if you feel like it). Get up and stay near the couch.
Now if only I wasnt letting the dogs in when this happened to me… (gf sidewalk)

You don’t need to lay there for hours, just stand up fast.
[/quote]

Stretch your hands to the ceiling after sitting for a long time. I have the tendency to stretch after a while so I do this by mistake after standing up too fast and it knocks me right out.[/quote]

It doesn’t knock me out, but sometimes when I stand up too fast I can’t see anything for like a second or two, although once I did it and was blind for about 5 or 6 seconds, freaked me out so much I was stumbling to the phone for an ambulance, obviously I didn’t get anywhere near it (due to duration and lack of sight)
